               <history>
                  <origin>
                     <origDate notBefore="1600" notAfter="1699">17th century</origDate> The
                     manuscript consists of 2 production units. <ref target="#p1"/> consisting of
                        <locus from="1" to="81"/> and <locus target="#84"/> is dated by Cerulli to
                        17th century. The date of <ref target="#p2"/> consisting of
                        <locus from="82" to="84"/> is unknown; it was sewn later to the codex. </origin>
                  
                  <provenance>The manuscript contains a long supplication in Amharic and Gǝʿǝz for
                        <persName ref="PRS15446SagaZaab"/>, written by <ref target="#h2"/>, on
                        <locus from="19vb" to="20rb"/>. Another
                     short supplication note for <persName ref="PRS15450WaldaMaryam"/> can be found
                     on <locus target="#67r"/>.</provenance>
               </history>
